What Will You Do?
The transport Process Engineering group is looking for a candidate to fulfill the role of Robotic and Process Engineer. The products we manufacture are part of virtually every type of telecom, enterprise, and data centre network. The processing expertise gained by our team over 20 years is progressing into the next-generation technologies. The successful candidate will be directly involved in process design cycle from conceptual design, a first build prototype in our lab, device characterization using both manual and automated equipment, to high volume production by one of our contract manufactures. The position resides in Ottawa Telecom Transport Business Unit, but frequent business travel to Asia is expected.
If you have a passion for learning and solving problems as well as an educational background that includes materials science, physics, engineering, programming or directly related disciplines; as well as hands-on experience in assembly processes and equipment setup; - this role could be just what you seek.
Responsibilities include but not limited to:
Design, develop and integration of robotics to different area of Mfg. Process including but not limited to advance packaging, automated epoxy application, automated machine vision application, soldering, and pick-and-place processes;
Specify the design and lead the assembly of tools and jigs. To assist with developing improved tooling and tool support strategies for manufacturing;
Sustain processes with emphasis on statistical process control, maintain yields and improve yields to targets. Improve manufacturability and defect reduction for different process areas of the fab by working closely with various process engineers;
Contribute to the transfer of new products to manufacturing sites and subsequent cost reductions;
Working within a cleanroom environment with the prerequisite use of cleanroom clothing;
Analysis of tool and process data with continuous improvement based on SPC and 6-sigma principles;
Equipment cross-qualification to ensure continuity of supply and to improve production capacity and cycle time;
Prepare and review technical documentation of procedures, publish results and provide training to technicians.
Requirements:
Bachelor or MSc degree in Robotics Engineering, Engineering Science, Materials Science, Physics or other relevant engineering or physical science discipline is required; PhD degree is an asset
Experience with Python, Machine vision solution method with use of Deep Learning and Artificial Intelligence
Experience working in a laboratory environment is necessary. Familiarity with components assemblies such as soldering, epoxy application, machining, designing tool to assist with the prototyping;
Familiarity with optoelectronic development from conceptual design, vendor interaction, package prototyping, testing, and performance characterization to NPI/volume production;
Familiarity in working with Contract Manufacturers (CM) and knowledge of assembly/test equipment capabilities (particularly in Asia), experience with automated assembly and test equipment;
Ability to work effectively with design engineers, manufacturing and external vendors to solve issues with optical components;
Strong written and oral communication skills;
Ability to travel internationally.
